-- Sebastian Vettel of Red Bull Wins Singapore Formula 1 Grand Prix
-- B y   B e n   P r i e c h e n f r i e d
-- 2013-09-22T14:14:10Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-09-22/sebastian-vettel-of-red-bull-wins-singapore-formula-1-grand-prix.html
Sebastian Vettel of Red Bull won
the Singapore Grand Prix today, his third straight victory, to
extend his lead in the Formula One drivers’ standings.  Ferrari’s Fernando Alonso was second and Lotus’s Kimi
Raikkonen third in the night race at the Marina Bay street
circuit.  Vettel, 26, has won seven of this season’s 13 races so far.
The German is seeking a fourth consecutive Formula One
championship.  The next race is in South Korea on Oct. 6, and the season
ends in Sao Paulo on Nov. 24.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Ben Priechenfried at the London Sports Desk  at  bprie@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
